- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also likely as the paper discusses the use of Wi-Fi signals for power delivery and the optimization of power transfer efficiency. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is another possible category as the paper presents a system for wireless power delivery and demonstrates its effectiveness in real-world conditions. 
- cs.MA (Multiagent Systems) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of Wi-Fi routers as a ubiquitous infrastructure for powering multiple devices. 
- cs.EM (Electromagnetism) is also a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses the use of Wi-Fi signals for wireless power delivery and the optimization of power transfer efficiency.
